{"actual_usd":0.155445,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":149,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30642,"reply":"\"I think the cross is necessary if God means to do more than wave sin away.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees, the morning light catching on the edge of my white tie while the square stays quiet around us.* \"If He simply overlooked evil, He wouldn't be merciful—He'd be indifferent. The cross is where mercy and truth meet: sin is named for the horror it is, and the sinner is not thrown away.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb along the worn edge of my Bible.* \"In plain terms—God doesn't forgive by pretending nothing happened. He forgives by bearing the cost Himself in Christ. That's the part that undoes me. What we're offered isn't cheap pardon. It's costly mercy.\"","rolling_24h_usd":56.38756500000002,"run_id":"9b913b70-55a2-4eef-ae8a-d2c58b7748db"}
